entries.meaning: A coonhound of a certain breed originating in the United States,

description: From blue +‎ tick. From the blue tick (check mark) shown when a message has been read on the app WhatsApp.

verbs.description: bluetick (third-person singular simple present blueticks, present participle blueticking, simple past and past participle blueticked)

entries.meaning: (Internet slang) To ignore (a message) sent via a social messaging app, especially one where a reply is expected or requested.
